# Stack Constraints

## Backend (NestJS)
- Framework: **NestJS only** — no Express without NestJS, no Fastify, no Koa
- ORM: **Prisma only** — no TypeORM, no Sequelize, no raw SQL strings
- Validation: **class-validator + class-transformer** — no Joi, no Zod on backend
- HTTP client: native fetch or axios — no got, no node-fetch
- Logging: **pino** — no winston, no console.log in production code
- Metrics: **prom-client** — no other metrics libraries
- Error tracking: **@sentry/node** — no other error tracking
- Testing: **Jest** — no Vitest on backend

## Frontend (Next.js)
- Framework: **Next.js App Router** — no Pages Router patterns, no Remix
- Server state: **TanStack Query** — no SWR, no Redux Toolkit Query, no React Query v3
- Forms: **React Hook Form + Zod** — no Formik, no controlled forms with useState
- UI components: **shadcn/ui** — no MUI, no Chakra, no Ant Design
- Styling: **Tailwind CSS** — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no emotion
- State management: none needed — if needed, use Zustand, NOT Redux

## Forbidden patterns
- No `any` type — use proper TypeScript types
- No `console.log` — use pino logger on backend
- No raw SQL — use Prisma client
- No hardcoded ports or URLs — use environment variables
- No `useState` for server state — use TanStack Query
